# Presentation HTML/CSS Standards

## Mobile-First & Responsive

- All new pages must be **mobile-friendly**
- Use `clamp()` for fluid typography: `clamp(min, preferred, max)`
- Add `@media (max-width: 768px)` for tablets/phones
- Add `@media (max-width: 480px)` for small phones
- Touch targets: minimum **44×44px** for buttons and links
- Add `-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent` on touch links
- Use `-webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch` for scrollable areas on iOS

## Viewport

Always include:
```html
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
```

## Slide Deck Specific

- Two-column layouts → single column on mobile (`grid-template-columns: 1fr` at 768px)
- Reduce slide padding on mobile (e.g. `4rem 5rem` → `1.5rem` horizontal)
- Add touch/swipe handlers for slide navigation on mobile
- Fixed nav (prev/next) must not overlap content; use `min-height` on slides for scroll clearance

## Structure

- Keep styles inline or in `<style>` (no external CSS for portability)
- Use relative links: `index.html`, `slides.html` (works on Netlify and local)
